commit.message: Release version 2.13.3

make: No longer add dash to ORG_LOAD_PATH

`ox-texinfo+' no longer depends on `dash'.
Fix typos
Release version 2.13.2

make: Remove release target

Going forward we only release to https://magit.vc/manual/magit-popup.
Add htmlxref.cnf
Release version 2.13.1

No longer depend on async package

We used to do that so that magit-popup would get properly recompiled
even when there are changes to macros and classes.  We don't need to
do that anymore because we are in maintenance mode and don't make such
changes anymore.  We remove this because it has bit-rotten; the format
of `async-bytecomp-allowed-packages' has changed, see #15.
Release version 2.13.0
manual: Prevent evaluation of code blocks
manual: Call ox-texinfo+-update-copyright-years while exporting
magit-invoke-popup: Don't insert help text into *Messages* buffer

magit-define-popup-option: Correct reader documentation

Fixes #11.
Release version 2.12.4
Clarify that you can set any variables in :variables
manual: Use a preamble to make initial text collapsible

magit-popup-format-action-button: Limit hiding of disabled command

If `disabled-command-function' is nil, then no command is
disabled, regardless of the value of their `disabled' property.
magit-popup-format-action-button: Hide disabled command
Fix name of license file

Revert "Revert "Remove Magit specific utility functions""

This reverts commit 4c05e829207355bf4b81608a50ce1ae0afe34e9c.

Document some advanced features

These features were added a long time ago and Magit uses them heavily.
They were not documented because they are rather hackish but that is
not a good reason.
make: Shorten some target descriptions
make: Remove deleted pages when publishing manual

Put library footer in separate section

This prevents it from being accidentally
removed when using `outline-minor-mode'.

Update .gitignore

Make it consistent with other such files in my other packages.

magit-popup-set-variable: Don't bother refreshing if unchanged

When working with a large buffer (e.g., a status buffer with a large
diff), calling `magit-refresh' can be an expensive operation.

Now, we'll only call `magit-refresh' when a variable's overall value
has actually changed (not just when its local configuration is set).

magit-popup-insert-section: Finalize heading before columns limit

Both the heading and the value of `:max-action-columns' can be
functions.  The latter is called with the heading as argument.
If the heading is a function then we turn it into a string first
making it much easier to match such a section.
Release version 2.12.2

Revert "Remove Magit specific utility functions"

This reverts commit 4c030aca025bcb7a39d43b0db758990963ca3b91.

Because Melpa-Stable always ships the latest version, we have
to restore some functions that are still required by the latest
Magit version.  Shortly before Magit 2.12.0 is released, these
functions can be removed again.
Release version 2.12.1
